ce:section.ce:para:
A one-pot hydrothermal method was applied for the ecological synthesis of FBEP-CQDs. This method relied on the treatment of cheap and available fava beans empty pods as a plant-based waste using microwave irradiation at 1700 W for 5 min (Fig. 1
                        ). The treatment time required by the microwave to synthesize FBEP-CQDs was studied. The QY has been estimated versus microwave irradiation time. It was observed that the increase of irradiation time from 3 min to 5 min enhanced the QY. Further increase of the microwave time to 6 min led to slightly decreased QY. Thus, 5 min was chosen as the optimum irradiation time as shown in Fig. 2

                        a.
